## Proposed Front‑End Architecture & Tasks
### 1. Project Scaffold
- Run `ng new mobile-service --style=scss`.
- Add Ionic: `ng add @ionic/angular`.
- Add Capacitor: `npx cap init mobile-service com.example.mobileservice`.
- Install dependencies: `@angular/router`, `@ngrx/store`, `socket.io-client`, `ngx-toastr`.

### 2. Global Styling & Design System
- Create `src/styles/_variables.scss` with color tokens, font families, spacing.
- Implement **glass‑morphism** card component (`src/app/shared/components/glass-card`).
- Set up dark‑mode toggle using CSS custom properties.
- Add Google Fonts via `index.html` link.

### 3. Core Pages & Components
| Feature | Component | Route |
|---|---|---|
| Authentication (login/register) | `auth/login`, `auth/register` | `/auth/login`, `/auth/register` |
| Device selection | `devices/select-device` | `/devices` |
| Service request form | `orders/create-order` | `/orders/new` |
| ETA modal | `orders/eta-modal` | (dialog) |
| Real‑time tracking | `orders/track-order` | `/orders/:id` |
| Feedback | `orders/feedback` | `/orders/:id/feedback` |
| Admin dashboard | `admin/*` (protected) | `/admin` |

### 4. API Integration
- Create `src/app/api` service layer using Angular `HttpClient`.
- AuthInterceptor to attach JWT.
- SocketService for real‑time updates.

### 5. Icons & Images
- Use Ionicons via `<ion-icon name="..."></ion-icon>`.
- Add Material Icons CDN for extra symbols.
- Generate placeholder hero and service images using the `generate_image` tool (e.g., `hero_banner`, `service_card`).

### 6. Responsive Design
- Use CSS Grid/Flexbox, media queries for breakpoints (mobile ≤ 640px, tablet ≤ 1024px, desktop > 1024px).
- Ensure Ionic components adapt automatically; test on Chrome dev tools and Android emulator.

### 7. Testing & Verification
- Unit tests with Jasmine/Karma for components.
- E2E tests with Cypress (web) and optionally Appium (mobile).
- Linting with ESLint + Stylelint.

